data.text:
Jerry Rubin (July 14, 1938 - November 28, 1994) was an activist author (Do It! – Scenarios of the Revolution; Yippie Manifesto; We Are Everywhere). Along with Abbie Hoffman, Rubin was probably the highest-profile leader of the Yippies.

He was one of the Chicago 8, which later became known as the Chicago 7.
